    Class Description
    Blinky
    Blinky is a ghost that behaves in a very aggressive manner towards a hunter.
    BoardItem
    BoardItem
    Clyde
    Clyde is a ghost that behaves in a very scared manner when close to a hunter.
    Direction
    Direction represents directions in a 2D plane.
    Entity
    Entity A entity is the animated objects in the game that can traverse the game board and interact with other entities.
    Ghost
    An Abstract Ghost which is a game entity.
    GhostType
    GhostType contains all the valid ghosts; the current list of ghosts are: "BLINKY", "CLYDE", "INKY", "PINKY".
    Hungry
    A Hungry hunter that has a special ability that allows the hunter to eat ghosts temporarily without them being in a Frightened state.
    Hunter
    Hunters are entities which are controlled by the player to clear the board and win the game.
    HunterType
    Definition of HunterType's available in the game.
    Inky
    Inky is a ghost that likes to tail close behind the hunter.
    Moveable
    An object that can move with a current position and a direction.
    PacmanBoard
    PacmanBoard
    Phase
    Phase Defines the different phases a ghost can be in.
    Phasey
    A Phasey hunter with a special ability that allows the hunter to travel through ghosts temporarily without dieing.
    Phil
    A Phil hunter that has no special ability.
    Pinky
    Pinky is a cunning ghost that tries to ambush the hunter.
    Position
    Similar to a Point Class but instead called Position.
    ScoreBoard
    ScoreBoard contains previous scores and the current score of the PacmanGame.
    Speedy
    A Speedy hunter that has a special ability that allows the hunter to travel twice as fast.
